Install it like this:

$ cd ~
$ rm -rf .vim/ .vimrc .gvimrc
$ git clone git://github.com/Osse/Vim-config.git .vim
$ git clone git://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git .vim/bundle/vundle

The configuration files .vimrc and .gvimrc are located inside the .vim
directory to making using the repo easier. To use them as your regular config
files for Vim, set up links to them like this:

$ cd ~
$ ln -s .vim/vimrc .vimrgc
$ ln -s .vim/gvimrc .gvimrc

After that, run :BundleInstall from within Vim. This makes Vundle automatically
install all the plugins listed in vimrc as 'bundles.'
